efore 1347","1330":"1330","1382":"1382","11 March 1397":"11 March 1397","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","19 January 1378":"19 January 1378","1378":"1378","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","March 1397":"March 1397","before May 1362":"before May 1362","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","Calais, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Calais, Pas-de-Calais, France","St peter of South Pederton, Somerset,England":"Somerset, England","Meriet, Somerest, England":"England, United Kingdom","Enfield, Middlesex, England":"Enfield, Middlesex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":12,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":37,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":50,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":104,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda married John Meriet before May 1362. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died on 11 March 1397, and was buried in Somerset, England."},"et":{"–11 March 1397":"–11. märts 1397","1328–1347":"1328–1347","1305–1378":"1305–1378","1330–1420":"1330–1420","1368–1410":"1368–1410","–1397":"–1397","before 1347":"enne 1347","1330":"1330","1382":"1382","11 March 1397":"11. märts 1397","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","19 January 1378":"19. jaanuar 1378","1378":"1378","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","March 1397":"märts 1397","before May 1362":"enne maid 1362","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","Calais, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","St peter of South Pederton, Somerset,England":"Somerset, England","Meriet, Somerest, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Enfield, Middlesex, England":"Enfield, Middlesex, England"},"fi":{"–11 March 1397":"–11. maaliskuuta 1397","1328–1347":"1328–1347","1305–1378":"1305–1378","1330–1420":"1330–1420","1368–1410":"1368–1410","–1397":"–1397","before 1347":"ennen vuotta 1347","1330":"1330","